ltsp (5.4.3-0ubuntu4+opinsys2) quantal; urgency=low

  * Run "update-initramfs -u -k all" with ltsp-client-core package.
    This is needed to ensure unbroken state of ltsp image.

 -- Opinsys Developers <dev@opinsys.fi>  Mon, 18 Mar 2013 15:00:26 +0200

ltsp (5.4.3-0ubuntu4+opinsys1) quantal; urgency=low

  * Do not trigger udhcp only because the kernel command line contains
    the word "ltsp".

 -- Juha Erkkilä <Juha.Erkkila@opinsys.fi>  Thu, 07 Feb 2013 14:57:00 +0200

ltsp (5.4.3-0ubuntu4) quantal; urgency=low

  * Upstream recently dropped the -a (architecture) flag of ltsp-update-image.
    Update the ltsp-server postinst to not try and call "-a i386" on Edubuntu.

 -- Stéphane Graber <stgraber@ubuntu.com>  Wed, 05 Sep 2012 16:52:47 -0400

ltsp (5.4.3-0ubuntu3) quantal; urgency=low

  * Fix ltsp-build-client producing a non-bootable system on x86 by
    fixing the update-initramfs hook to check for param.conf before trying
    to sed it. Cherry picked commit (r2391) from upstream.
  * Change default color depth from 16bit to 24bit as 16bit just doesn't
    work when using unity with llvmpipe. This is a workaround and alternatives
    should be looked at to get back to 16bit if possible.

 -- Stéphane Graber <stgraber@ubuntu.com>  Thu, 30 Aug 2012 17:10:29 -0700

ltsp (5.4.3-0ubuntu2) quantal; urgency=low

  * ltsp-client-builder:
    - Fix fat-client option to actually work (instead of always building
      fat client images)
    - Add --updates-mirror none to fix install failure when media doesn't
      contain an updates pocket

 -- Stéphane Graber <stgraber@ubuntu.com>  Thu, 30 Aug 2012 14:13:10 -0700

ltsp (5.4.3-0ubuntu1) quantal; urgency=low

  * New upstream release (5.4.3)
    - Background jetpipe (LP: #996533)
    - Support armhf target, building an omap4 image and pxelinux structure.
    - Install ltsp-sound.rules directly in /usr/share/ltsp/udev/
  * Drop --mount-cdrom from ltsp-client-builder flags.

