  * new upstream version (5.1.38)
   * introduce screen-session.d
   * RandR support

 -- Stéphane Graber <stgraber@ubuntu.com>  Thu, 11 Dec 2008 21:44:06 -0800

ltsp (5.1.35-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * new upstream version:
    - xinitrc.d hooks:
      + x keyboard settings 
      + DPMS/screen blanking
    - drop use of configure_localdev function in ltsp-client-core init script
    - Add ltsp-cluster scripts
    - allow an arbitrary number of mirrors. based on patch by Raman
      Pandarinathan.
    - ltsp-update-sshkeys: don't require chroot to be present
  * depend on ltspfsd >= 0.5.3, which handles cdpinger and ltspfsd without
    calls from ltsp init scripts.
  * use proper VCS-* headers
  * add debian/watch file explaining how to find current released version.

