ltsp (5.0.8debian1) unstable; urgency=low

  * sync with upstream:
      - support unencrypted LDM logins (LDM_DIRECTX)
      - generate debian/control to reduce Debian/Ubuntu conflicts

  * sync with Ubuntu:
      - local printer support (jetpipe)
      - pulseaudio sound system

  * split ltsp-client into ltsp-client-core and ltsp-client
      - all features (sound/localdev) enabled by default

  * use proper boolean handling for NETWORK_COMPRESSION, based on patch from
    Tim Day.  (Closes: #421324)

  * Add code in the ltsp-client-builder udeb and a ltsp-client-builder plugin
    to pass the d-i keyboard setting to LTSP and X.org. Thanks Petter.
    (Closes: #421762)

  * sound dependencies moved from ltsp-server to ltsp-server-standalone.
    (Closes: #356986)

  * drop support for obsoleted packages from debian sarge

